body:
@KopfKrieg

> If you define your filetype using the extension (like .jpg), it's a bad design because it can fail. The „right“ way to create a file type based compression would be to look into the files header (first few bytes) and then decide,

Theoretically, sure, if someone names the file wrong, but so what?  Compressing based on file extensions would work well 99% of the time, and in the corner cases it would just take a little longer.
